Class Configuration

  • java.lang.Object
    • sailpoint.tools.xml.AbstractXmlObject

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Cacheable, sailpoint.tools.xml.PersistentXmlObject, sailpoint.tools.xml.XMLReferenceTarget

    public class Configuration
extends SailPointObject
implements java.lang.Cloneable, Cacheable
    Class to hold extensible configuration parameters.

    An instance of this class named "SystemConfiguration" holds many configuration parameters presented in the UI under the "System Setup" tab.

    Most of the name constants defined in this class are key names in the system configuration object.

      • LOCK_TIMEOUT

        public static final java.lang.String LOCK_TIMEOUT
        Default number of minutes a persistent lock will be held. This is relevant only for objects locked with the Persistent option as opposed to the Transaction option. This is used by the aggregation and refresh tasks to synchronize access to an Identity.

        For most of the timeouts, zero means "never" but that is never what you want here. If a lock is left dangling by accident, it must timeout at some point. If the number is negative or zero it defaults to LockInfo.DEFAULT_LOCK_TIMEOUT which is currently 5.

        See Also:
